    <h2 id="section-2">Order Of Disclaimers And Disclosures</h2>
    <p>When the content has multiple <a href="https://brandcentral.bmfoc.zone/quicken-loans/legal/disclaimer-library.htm">disclaimers and disclosures</a>, stack them in this order:</p>
    <ol>
        <li>Disclaimers or disclosures about the specific loan product or thing we're advertising</li>
        <li>J.D. Power disclaimer, if needed</li>
        <li>Any opt-out disclosures</li>
        <li>The National Licensing Disclosure, if needed</li>
        <li>Copyright for single-line address (add an email only)</li>
    </ol>
    <h2>Trademarks, Service Marks, Registered Symbols And Copyright Symbols</h2>
    <p>The symbols let others know that we're claiming exclusivity and trademark protection, so putting the marks and symbols in prominent places is key to protecting our brand.</p>
    <p><strong>In general, place the mark or symbol on first reference of the term in the copy of the creative.</strong> If the term is in the headline, include the mark or symbol in the headline as the first reference. This guidance is for copy mentions only. We do not use marks or symbols on logos, intentionally.</p>
    <p><em>Ex. With a Rocket Mortgage<sup>®</sup>&nbsp;refi, you could save on your monthly payment. Sign in to Rocket Mortgage to get started.</em></p>
    <h2 id="section-2a">Style Notes</h2>
    <p>Place trademarks, service marks and registered symbols before end punctuation and/or end quotation marks.&nbsp;</p>
    <p><em>Ex. Get started with Rocket Mortgage<sup>®</sup>.</em></p>
    <p>Place copyright symbols directly before the terms they're referring to; don't include a space after the symbol.</p>
    <p><em>Ex. ©2000 - 2021 Rocket Mortgage, LLC.</em></p>
    <p><strong>Why did we move away from placing the mark or symbol on each use of the term in the copy?</strong></p>
    <p>With multiple marks and symbols dotting creative, the content became difficult to read and digest for clients and served more as a distraction. By only using marks and symbols on the first reference of the term, we provide clean and streamlined content and design, and it doesn't impact our ability to defend our use of the marks.</p>
    <p><strong>How does this apply to Rocket Homes? Right now, we use “Rocket Homes Real Estate LLC” on first reference and “Rocket Homes<sup>®</sup>” on all subsequent references. Would it be “Rocket Homes Real Estate LLC” on first reference, “Rocket Homes<sup>®</sup>” on second reference and “Rocket Homes” alone on all subsequent references?</strong></p>
    <p>Yes, Rocket Homes Real Estate LLC should still be used on first instance and then this rule would follow for each instance after. The first Rocket Homes should have an r-ball.</p>
